    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Cynara scolymus are antioxidant, which is attributed to its flavonoids and phenolic acids, and anti-inflammatory properties, resulting from its saponins and terpenoids, that can modulate the activity of various enzymes and cytokines, thereby reducing oxidative stress and inflammation in the body. Additionally, this plant possesses antimicrobial properties, mediated by its essential oils and phenolic compounds, that are effective against a wide range of microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi. Cynara scolymus also exhibits hypoglycemic effects, which are associated with its flavonoids and terpenoids, that can inhibit glucose uptake in the intestines and improve insulin sensitivity. Furthermore, its cardioprotective properties are attributed to its flavonoids and saponins, that can reduce lipid peroxidation and improve cardiovascular function by modulating the activity of various enzymes and receptors. The bioactive compounds present in Cynara scolymus, including flavonoids, saponins, and essential oils, are responsible for its medicinal properties, which can be used to prevent and treat various diseases.",
