    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Cynara scolymus are cynarin, quercetin, luteolin, kaempferol, and apigenin. These constituents have been identified as responsible for the medicinal properties of artichoke extract. Cynarin has been shown to improve liver function by increasing bile production, reducing bilirubin levels, and inhibiting lipid peroxidation. Flavonoids such as quercetin, luteolin, kaempferol, and apigenin possess antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and anti-cancer properties, which contribute to the plant's hepatoprotective and anti-arthritic effects. Research has demonstrated that these flavonoids inhibit enzymes involved in the inflammatory response, reduce oxidative stress, and induce apoptosis in cancer cells.",
