    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Cynara scolymus are derived from its edible flower buds and leaves, which have been used in traditional medicine for various purposes. Infusion and tea preparations are made from the dried flowers and leaves, often used to support digestive health and reduce inflammation. Tincture preparations are typically made from the dried flowers and leaves, which are extracted with a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin, used to treat various health conditions including liver and kidney support. Salve preparations are made from the leaves and flowers, used topically to soothe skin irritations and wounds. Artichoke capsules are a concentrated form of the herb, used to support liver and cardiovascular health.",
